Q35. What's your approach to prompt engineering for agents?\
\
A: I treat prompts like code \'97 versioned, tested, iterated. Key practices:\
- Concrete examples > abstract descriptions in system prompts\
- Explicit output schema with a JSON example, not just field descriptions\
- Separate system prompt (role/context) from task prompt (current input)\
- Test prompt changes against an eval set before shipping\
\
Example:\
    Bad system prompt:\
        "Return a JSON with root_cause, confidence, and fix fields."\
\
    Good system prompt:\
        "Return ONLY valid JSON in this exact format:\
         \{\
           'root_cause': 'brief description of what caused the issue',\
           'confidence': 0.87,\
           'fix': 'specific remediation step'\
         \}\
         No explanation, no markdown, no extra fields."\
\
    Second version cuts JSON parse failures from 15% to under 1%.\
\
