Q36. How do you handle cost and latency optimization in LLM-heavy pipelines?\
\
A: \
- Semantic caching for repeated/similar queries\
- Use smaller/faster models for low-complexity nodes (routing, classification)\
- Reserve large models (GPT-4/Claude) for reasoning-heavy nodes only\
- Batch tool calls where possible instead of sequential\
- Monitor token usage per node to find expensive bottlenecks\
\
Example:\
    Before optimization:\
        Every node uses GPT-4 \uc0\u8594  avg run cost $0.08, latency 8s\
\
    After optimization:\
        Routing node:    GPT-3.5  (classify intent, simple task)\
        Enrichment node: GPT-3.5  (structured extraction)\
        Reasoning node:  GPT-4    (complex diagnosis only)\
        + semantic cache hits 40% of repeat queries\
        \uc0\u8594  avg run cost $0.02, latency 3.5s\
\
