Q: Straggler Handling\
Another challenging piece was 
\f1\b straggler handling in OpenFL's Federated Learning framework
\f2\b0  \'97 two merged PRs in the official repository.\

\f1\b The Problem:
\f2\b0  In distributed FL, a training round can't complete until all collaborating nodes finish their tasks. One slow node \'97 a straggler \'97 blocks every other node and tanks throughput. \
There was no mechanism to handle this. The framework just waited indefinitely.\

\f1\b Why it was hard:
\f2\b0 \
The fix sounds simple \'97 add a timeout. But FL training rounds are stateful and cyclical. The core challenge was: 
\f3\fs26 threading.Timer
\f2\fs24  can only be started once per object. \
So every round, you can't just restart the same timer \'97 you have to delete the old object and instantiate a new one. Getting this lifecycle wrong meant the policy either fired at the \
wrong time, didn't fire at all, or leaked memory across rounds.\
On top of that, the Aggregator wasn't tracking which collaborators had finished 
\f1\b all
\f2\b0  tasks vs. just one task. Without fixing that, the cutoff logic would trigger prematurely \'97 \
cutting off nodes that were mid-task, not actually stragglers.\
There was also a thread-safety issue \'97 multiple collaborators reporting results concurrently could race on the shared completion state. Had to introduce a 
\f3\fs26 Lock
\f2\fs24  around collaborator tracking.\

\f1\b How I solved it:
\f2\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Added a 
\f3\fs26 start_policy
\f2\fs24  interface to 
\f3\fs26 StragglerHandlingFunction
\f2\fs24  so policies are pluggable\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Implemented 
\f3\fs26 CutoffTimeBasedStragglerHandling
\f2\fs24  with 
\f3\fs26 threading.Timer
\f2\fs24  \'97 timer fires a callback after cutoff, which applies the policy only if minimum reporting threshold is met\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Fixed the Aggregator to track collaborators that completed 
\f1\b all
\f2\b0  assigned tasks, not just the first one\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
